Response ID: resp_2409
Response Text: In general I think moving all aspects of culture and the arts under ACME is a good first step. We have been separate communities for way too long. But this transition will require a high level of transparence and communication. I think a large focus on websites and digital communication will be KEY. Clear communication as we all panic about sharing pots of money is going to be important. There will also need to be a considerable amount of listening to all cultural entities. Just looking at this form I didn't feel like those of us in the Historic Preservation community were represented on the front page of this form. Historic Museums and spaces are a huge part of the culture of Austin. Many of whom use their spaces as venues for music and performance.

